sql:
SELECT title, difficulty
FROM problems
ORDER BY difficulty ASC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT problem_id) AS total_solved_problems
FROM problem_attempts
WHERE solved = 1;

SELECT title
FROM problems
ORDER BY title ASC;

SELECT COUNT(problem_id) AS solved_problems
FROM problem_attempts
WHERE user_id = 1 AND solved = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Top 5 problems with the highest acceptance rates means those problems with the highest percentage of people solving them correctly; 
- Top users refers to those who have made the most attempts and had the fastest average time; 
- Attempts refer to the number of times a user tried to solve a problem.

